---
description: UI/component conventions. Apply when building or changing user-facing frontend code.
globs:
  - "**/*.tsx"
  - "**/*.jsx"
  - "**/*.vue"
  - "**/*.svelte"
alwaysApply: false
---

Opt-in frontend discipline. Localization should delete this file if the project has no UI, or replace the generic guidance with the project's real component, state, and styling conventions.

- Reuse the existing component library, design tokens, and styling system. Don't introduce a second way to do the same thing.
- Do not introduce a new styling system unless the project already uses it or the user explicitly approves it.
- Handle every state: loading, empty, error, and success. Don't ship the happy path alone.
- Make interactive elements accessible: real semantics, keyboard support, focus states, and labels for assistive tech.
- Keep components focused. Extract a subcomponent or hook when one grows too large or mixes concerns.
- Derive UI from state; avoid duplicating server data into local state that can drift.
- Match existing data-fetching, error-handling, and form-validation patterns rather than inventing new ones.
